# ZITADEL Integration Example

This project demonstrates how to integrate ZITADEL into your application. It includes an example of an `echo` endpoint `/userinfo` that uses ZITADEL middleware to check access permissions.

## Features

- Middleware to validate access tokens using ZITADEL.
- Secure `userinfo` endpoint to retrieve user information.

## Prerequisites

- A ZITADEL account.
- A configured ZITADEL project with the necessary API permissions.

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-repo/zitadel-example.git
   cd zitadel-example
   ```

2. Install dependencies:

   ```bash
   go mod tidy
   ```

3. Set up environment variables:
   ```bash
   export ZITADEL_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
   export ZITADEL_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
   export ZITADEL_ISSUER=https://your-zitadel-instance
   ```

